<h1>Problem 1308 - 2022 Taiwan IMOC, G5, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>\(P\) is a point inside \(ABC\). \(BP\), \(CP\) intersect \(AC, AB\) at \(E, F\), respectively. \(AP\) intersect \(\odot (ABC)\) again at X. \(\odot (ABC)\) and \(\odot (AEF)\) intersect again at \(S\). \(T\) is a point on \(BC\) such that \(P T \parallel EF\). Prove that \(\odot (ST X)\) passes through the midpoint of \(BC\).</p>
